1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,680
What if I agree to marry him?

2
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,120
Pin agreed?

3
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:27,760
I love you the most, Auntie.

4
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,440
<i>I don't want money.</i>

5
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,880
But I want to end someone's life.

6
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:42,120
You've already got the money.

7
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,320
What else do you want?

8
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,040
Both your lives!

9
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,240
Kill them!

10
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,480
Take them alive.

11
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,880
We need them as witnesses.

12
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,200
Hey! Fall back!

13
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,480
Hey. Yai!

14
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,840
Yai!

15
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,280
Yai! Are you okay?

16
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:50,360
Mr. Yai.

17
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,880
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

18
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:56,360
Mr. Yai.

19
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,480
Mr. Yai.

20
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,760
Mr. Yai, you're not dead?

21
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,520
Right now, I'm about to be.

22
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,680
Mr. Yai.

23
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:06,600
No.

24
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,680
You can't die.

25
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,640
If you do, I'll remarry.

26
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,880
No way. Don't even think about it.

27
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,839
With bulletproof vests,

28
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,079
it's hard to die.

29
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,600
Anyway,

30
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,200
how did you get here, Mr. Yai?

31
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:32,320
Where have you been?
You didn't even take your phone.

32
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,600
What if Pin had something urgent come up?

33
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:39,360
I hurried out to get something important
to expose Madam Krongsuk,

34
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,760
so I completely forgot.

35
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,600
<i>Mr. Yai, I need your help urgently.</i>

36
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,280
<i>You didn't tell me where you were,</i>

37
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,600
so I guessed it had to be

38
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,200
around Tong's warehouse
where he once locked Nee up.

39
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:59,080
Luckily, I saw the lady's car
parked right at the entrance.

40
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,080
And how did you survive?

41
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,560
How I survived can wait.

42
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:10,200
Just keep the fact
that you saw me a secret.

43
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,480
Now you know

44
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,240
how Madam Krongsuk and Mr. Tong

45
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,160
have been working together
doing all those terrible things.

46
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:23,800
You can report them to the police.

47
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,080
It won't be hard
for the police to investigate.

48
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,880
They murdered your caretaker

49
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,920
and kidnapped you from the farm.

50
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,200
Just bring in
one of Mr. Tong's former henchmen,

51
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,320
and he'll spill who ordered everything.

52
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,400
It's fine.

53
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,600
I don't want it to escalate.

54
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:45,120
I won't tell the police
about what happened between us.

55
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,320
I promise.

56
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,280
But…

57
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,720
Thank you.

58
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:56,640
But I think it's best
if everything ends here.

59
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,720
Let's go, Mom.

60
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,600
I want to see Jan.

61
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,400
Let's go.

62
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,640
Thank you all so much.

63
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,720
You too.

64
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,640
You're a very brave woman.

65
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,960
Let's go, Mom.

66
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,600
Let's go.

67
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,240
Why didn't you want to report it?

68
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:46,680
Don't you want the person
who killed Jan to get arrested?

69
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,880
Jan died because of me.

70
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:55,640
What do you mean by that?

71
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,040
What happened?

72
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:03,000
It must have been
someone close to us, right?

73
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:07,120
When I called Tatsana and his aunt,
no one wanted to help you.

74
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,440
Na knows about this, doesn't he?

75
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,920
I don't know.

76
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:13,880
I don't know.

77
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,840
And I don't want to know anything anymore.

78
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,400
Fine.

79
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,520
Go to the police station.
I'm going to file a report.

80
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,480
No, Mom.

81
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:26,320
I want to go home.

82
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,000
I don't want to go there. Don't go.

83
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,360
Please.

84
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:33,320
You may not want to know, but I do.

85
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:35,960
Go.

86
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,200
Mom,

87
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:39,120
I can't take anything anymore.

88
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,200
Please.

89
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,560
Don't go.

90
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,000
On.

91
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,840
On.

92
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,200
What's wrong?

93
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,160
On.

94
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,560
On.

95
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,320
Go to the hospital!

96
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,240
On.

97
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,400
On.

98
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:29,320
Are you still mad at me?

99
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,799
I really don't understand you.

100
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:36,280
Why do you keep doing
such dangerous things?

101
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,840
You never learn.

102
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,919
If you couldn't call me,
you could've called Pan or Chief Yam.

103
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,440
It happened so suddenly.

104
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,480
I didn't want to trouble the chief.

105
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,440
And Mr. Pan just lost Aunt Pen.

106
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,000
I didn't want him risking himself.

107
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,520
So you went in alone,

108
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,760
trying to be a heroine?

109
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,680
I only want to be your woman.

110
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:00,840
Wait. Don't try to sweet-talk me.

111
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:02,240
I'm not going to soften up.

112
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,840
I'm serious.

113
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:08,280
I feel like
the luckiest woman in the world

114
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,280
to have you as my husband.

115
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,080
Compared to Ms. On…

116
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,440
I feel sorry for her.

117
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,000
Hey.

118
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:24,600
Puny Pin.

119
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:27,000
Onsa-ang tried to kill you.

120
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,080
At first, I was angry.

121
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:34,080
But when I saw
the person she loved abandon her

122
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,240
and refuse
to even risk his life to help her,

123
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,120
my heart hurt for her.

124
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,760
People are like boats
in the middle of the sea.

125
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,560
We have to face storms sometimes.

126
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:00,840
Onsa-ang has to find her own way
to reach the shore.

127
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,200
Just like me.

128
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,560
If I hadn't met you,

129
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:10,760
I'd probably be sitting
in prison right now

130
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,200
from killing that madam.

131
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,000
If I hadn't met you,

132
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:22,200
I'd probably have a simple family
with some villager nearby.

133
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:24,680
Hey.

134
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,440
You think I'd let you marry someone else?

135
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,760
I've had my eye on you
since you first grew into a young woman.

136
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,800
This is my wife.

137
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,000
Big talk.

138
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,920
You never even courted me.

139
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,280
Courting is no fun.

140
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,760
Kissing is better.

141
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,280
Mr. Yai.

142
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,320
Come here.

143
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,640
I believe you now.

144
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,240
Hey, Mr. Yai.

145
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,440
Come here.

146
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,440
- Come here.
- Auntie.

147
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,760
Take this!

148
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,560
Stay out of this, you wimp.

149
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,320
Hey.

150
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,840
Tell me the truth.

151
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,560
Did you send someone to rescue On

152
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,280
and steal the ransom money?

153
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,720
Why would I do that?

154
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,000
I'm your woman.

155
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,960
You'd share the money with me anyway.

156
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:11,600
You liar.

157
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:16,160
You used On to trick me
into eliminating your enemies.

158
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:18,040
You poisonous snake.

159
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:19,600
You deserve to die.

160
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,080
- Don't.
- Na.

161
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,200
Na.

162
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,200
What the hell is all that shouting?
It's already hard for me to sleep.

163
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,400
What is this?

164
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,480
What now?

165
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,560
Just a moment ago, you looked so tough.

166
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,720
Now you're nothing

167
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,440
but crippled.

168
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,400
What did you do to me?

169
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:18,240
I just put poison
into your coffee every day

170
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,800
since the day you came to the farm.

171
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,000
You fool.

172
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:26,640
Did you really think
I'd split the inheritance with you?

173
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:28,440
Auntie…

174
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:44,360
Go get the documents envelope
from the desk in my office.

175
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:46,880
Now.

176
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,480
Hurry.

177
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:05,400
Take them out and make him sign them.

178
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,440
Use your last chance in life

179
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,800
to sign over your house,

180
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,720
assets,

181
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,760
and all your businesses to me.

182
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:21,880
Then I'll give you the antidote.

183
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,840
After that,

184
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:26,760
I'll send you off
to a neighboring country.

185
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,960
That way, we can part on good terms.

186
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:33,680
I worked my whole life to earn that money.

187
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,680
You think
you can just suck it away that easily?

188
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,480
Your money?

189
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,520
It's all gamblers' money.

190
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,200
So are you going to sign or not?

191
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:44,640
If not, then get ready to go to Hell.

192
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,560
You fool!

193
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:47,960
Stop!

194
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:49,680
Hey!

195
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:51,760
Sommai, help me.

196
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,280
This bitch betrayed me.

197
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,280
Hey.

198
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,200
Hey.

199
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,800
You're still taking orders from him?

200
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:02,960
He's the one
who sent other people to take On

201
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:06,360
and then ordered them
to silence all of you too.

202
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:14,040
That's why I had to protect myself
and deal with him first.

203
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:17,040
No wonder you didn't go with us.

204
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,880
Don't believe her.

205
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:21,400
She's framing me. You bitch!

206
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,680
Look at him.

207
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,960
And you'd still let him
keep ordering you around?

208
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,320
Come work for me.

209
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,240
And you'll be in charge
of all his businesses.

210
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:45,000
Mr. Tong, just sign them.

211
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,920
- Don't believe her.
- Sign.

212
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,520
Sign them properly.

213
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,240
I know exactly
what your signature looks like.

214
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,600
Don't try to trick me.

215
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:19,040
Take him somewhere comfortable.

216
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,280
Go ahead.

217
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,680
Where are you taking me?

218
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,840
What about the antidote? The antidote.

219
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,200
Antidote?

220
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:30,720
There's no such thing, you fool.

221
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,720
You bitch.

222
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:37,000
I never should've trusted you.

223
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:39,120
You'll die a horrible death, Krongsuk!

224
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,840
Mr. Yai went to drop Pin off
and hasn't come back yet.

225
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:18,760
Phong, wait here.

226
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:19,840
I'll go in and get him.

227
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:22,600
Be careful, Mr. Pan.

228
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:23,920
Yeah.

229
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,600
What the hell are you doing?

230
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:05,160
You came after me to kill me, didn't you?

231
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,880
Go ahead. Kill me.

232
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,960
I already want to die. Do it!

233
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:11,079
I don't want to see
that woman's face anymore!

234
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:13,200
She's not my mother! She's a monster!

235
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,079
Go on. Kill me!

236
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:17,400
Kill me!

237
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,880
I'm scared.

238
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,440
Here. See?

239
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:02,040
It sends the intercepted audio signal
to the phone like this.

240
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,840
If there's anything you don't understand,
you can check the manual.

241
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,040
Alright.

242
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:10,720
I understand now.

243
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:15,360
Madam and Mr. Tong aren't home right now.

244
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,480
They're probably at the gambling den.

245
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:20,560
I'll hurry and install the bug
in Madam's room.

246
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:22,600
You should go back now.

247
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,520
Now that I think about it,

248
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,200
going back and forth is riskier.

249
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:31,600
I should just stay hidden in this room.

250
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,640
If anything happens,
I can help you faster.

251
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,120
Mr. Yai.

252
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:40,080
Don't be stubborn.

253
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,000
You can't stay here.

254
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,360
Don't put on an act.

255
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,120
Get up right now.

256
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:52,520
Pin.

257
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:58,440
Mr. Yai, you're getting ridiculous.

258
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:00,520
Not ridiculous.

259
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:04,160
At this level, I'm solid, strong,
and ready for any situation.

260
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,120
Pervert.

261
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:08,480
Mr. Yai, don't be so loud.

262
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,520
Then I'll whisper instead.

263
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,280
Did you miss me?

264
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:29,000
Only a little?

265
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,320
I missed you so much.

266
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,040
Pin,

267
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,480
I'm worried about you.

268
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:25,440
We can still stop now.

269
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:27,240
I'll find a way
to help Uncle Pload myself,

270
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,600
so you won't have
to risk your life for me.

271
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,080
I'm doing this for Mom and Aunt Pen.

272
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:39,120
Justice exists.

273
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:45,120
Whoever does wrong
must be punished by the law.

274
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:50,000
I thought you'd be kind enough
to forgive others easily.

275
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:58,040
Forgiveness only has value
when that person truly repents.

276
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,600
I have to go now.

277
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,680
Don't look at me like that.

278
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:28,400
Or I might drag you into round two.

279
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:35,280
I was going to tell you
to take care of yourself.

280
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,360
You too.

281
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:51,040
Ms. Jin, did you find my dad?

282
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,560
<i>Yes.</i>

283
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,440
Uncle Win is fine.

284
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:56,160
And I already told him

285
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:58,920
that you've gone off to be a lackey
for a bunch of society's trash.

286
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,400
Don't use Dad to threaten me, Ms. Jin.

287
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,160
Even if he comes here, I'm not leaving.

288
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:49,440
Mr. Yai.

289
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:51,400
Dad?

290
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,680
Uncle Win.

291
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:56,320
- Hey, come here.
- Hey.

292
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:58,040
- Come here. Run.
- Hey.

293
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:00,200
Dad.

294
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,360
Dad.

295
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:05,480
Dad.

296
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:07,400
Uncle Win. Let go of me.
I'm going to check on Uncle Win.

297
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:10,080
Yai. Run first. We have to fall back.

298
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,360
- Go.
- Uncle Win.

299
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,680
How is Uncle Win?

300
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:23,960
Mr. Yai asked me to come ask.

301
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,400
The bullet didn't hit any vital areas.

302
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,680
He's safe now.

303
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,360
What about Jom?

304
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:34,480
Uncle Win told the police
the gun went off by accident.

305
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,440
Jom asked the police for a little time.

306
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:37,840
He'll turn himself in this evening.

307
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,920
Pin, where have you been?

308
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,320
I'm sorry, Dad.

309
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,120
Please forgive me.

310
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:17,240
So you do know how to feel regret?

311
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:20,000
If you knew right from wrong,

312
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,600
you wouldn't have gone
to work for that heartless madam.

313
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,520
Then who was that man in black?

314
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:42,960
Why did you take the bullet for him?

315
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:45,560
You almost made me become
a son who killed his own father.

316
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:47,760
Don't ask anything.

317
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:53,680
I'll hire a lawyer
and fight the case for you myself.

318
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,400
But don't go back
to that madam ever again.

319
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,040
No.

320
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:03,000
If you won't tell me
who that man in black was,

321
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:06,520
then I won't do what you say.

322
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,800
If you're going
to keep serving evil people…

323
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,080
then we are

324
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,400
no longer father and son.

325
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:22,440
Go. Don't ever show your face to me again.

326
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,160
Dad…

327
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:50,880
Uncle Win wanted me
to tell you not to worry

328
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:53,520
and not to blame yourself.

329
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:57,280
If Uncle Win dies because of me,
I'll never forgive myself.

330
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,720
Why did he have to do that?

331
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,520
My life isn't worth that much.

332
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:05,080
Uncle Win didn't do it for you.

333
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:06,760
He did it for Jom.

334
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:09,600
He didn't want Jom to become a murderer.

335
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:13,200
Even if it hadn't been you,
he still would've done the same thing.

336
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:22,360
If you button the first button wrong,

337
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,040
the rest will be off too.

338
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:26,640
Another proverb?

339
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:29,880
If you want to say I'm the cause
of everything bad, then just say it.

340
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:32,760
Scolding you now won't do any good.

341
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:36,000
I want to help,
but I don't even know how to help.

342
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:38,840
It's like a monkey
trying to untangle a fishing net.

343
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:46,520
You come say confusing proverbs
and then leave.

344
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:48,520
You're always like this.

345
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:55,640
- Hey?
- Mr. Na.

346
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:58,840
Why did you call me here?

347
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:01,040
Pin.

348
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,440
I have some savings.

349
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:08,440
It should be enough to rent a small house
for four or five months.

350
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,360
During that time, I'll find work.

351
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:14,600
You can just find some light work
and stay at home.

352
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,080
I'll take care of you myself.

353
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,040
Wait, Mr. Na.

354
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:19,400
I don't understand.

355
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,680
What do you mean?

356
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:23,840
Run away with me, Pin.

357
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:27,000
I can't stay here anymore. I'm scared.

358
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:28,760
Mr. Na.

359
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:31,080
You're scared? Scared of what?

360
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:33,120
Mr. Tong?

361
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,560
You can tell me, Mr. Na.

362
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:37,720
So where did Mr. Tong disappear to?

363
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:39,360
Why haven't I seen him recently?

364
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:40,960
I don't know.

365
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:44,640
But we have to leave right now,

366
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,200
before Auntie comes back.

367
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:48,880
Wait, Mr. Na. Tell me.

368
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:51,760
Let's go first. I'll tell you later, Pin.

369
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:54,400
- Let's go.
- Mr. Na. No. I'm not going.

370
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:05,600
You never really wanted
to marry me, did you?

371
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,520
You came back…

372
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,320
because of this thing, didn't you?

373
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,880
Why were you trying
to listen in on Auntie?

374
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:40,160
I don't know
what Madam really thinks of me,

375
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:42,520
so I had to be careful.

376
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,680
Then,

377
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,840
run away with me,

378
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:50,800
and you won't have to be afraid anymore.

379
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:54,240
We'll start a new life together, Pin.

380
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,960
Mr. Na,

381
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,600
aren't you worried about Madam at all?

382
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:01,200
She loves you very much.

383
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:18,760
She doesn't really love me.

384
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:22,280
All she wants is money.

385
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:25,120
That's not true.

386
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,760
From what I've seen,

387
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:32,360
you've received so much love from Madam.

388
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,960
More than my mother ever loved me.

389
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,640
More than Ms. Nee.

390
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,160
More than anyone.

391
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:45,440
How much more do you want
before it's enough?

392
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,080
How much?

393
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,960
As much as a mother…

394
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:02,160
can love her child.

395
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,480
She won't even let me

396
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:11,280
call her Mom, Pin.

397
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:27,680
Mr. Na.

398
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:34,360
I can't endure
staying with Auntie anymore.

399
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,160
I'm scared, Pin.

400
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:39,800
Pin.

401
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,240
Please take me

402
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:44,280
away from here.

403
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,800
I understand you, Mr. Na.

404
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,680
But running away won't solve anything.

405
00:30:58,720 --> 00:30:59,920
I've already decided.

406
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:04,480
We can be together,
without Auntie controlling us anymore.

407
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:08,520
I can't wait any longer, Pin.

408
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:09,920
Let's go right now.

409
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,760
Mr. Na, but I can't go with you right now.

410
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,360
If you won't come,

411
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:20,720
I'll give the listening device to Auntie.

412
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:23,640
Please don't, Mr. Na.

413
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:26,440
You won't go with me

414
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:30,000
because you still can't forget Yai, right?

415
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:31,680
No, that's not it.

416
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,120
Why, Pin?

417
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:36,200
Why do you still love him,

418
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:38,600
even though he mistreated you?

419
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:39,760
Tell me.

420
00:31:39,840 --> 00:31:41,200
Why, Pin? Pin!

421
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,600
Mr. Na.

422
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,000
Mr. Yai?

423
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:49,920
Mr. Yai,

424
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:52,040
how did you get in here?

425
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,480
It's dangerous here.

426
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:56,560
He was threatening you. I had no choice.

427
00:31:56,640 --> 00:31:57,880
Mr. Yai.

428
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:59,320
Jom is coming this way.

429
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:01,680
Run now.

430
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,160
I'll buy you some time.

431
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:04,800
Go.

432
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:07,400
Pin.

433
00:32:08,320 --> 00:32:09,600
I saw that masked man run this way.

434
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,320
He knocked Mr. Na out and ran off.

435
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:14,560
Which way did he go?

436
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:16,400
- This way.
- That way.

437
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:19,880
This way.

438
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:27,480
Jom, not that way. Jom.

439
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:02,360
Where's the masked man?

440
00:33:02,880 --> 00:33:05,600
I chased him this far,
and then he vanished.

441
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:08,800
You, go that way.

442
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,800
Search everywhere. Go!

443
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,000
You have so many guards,

444
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,600
yet you still let him
sneak into the house?

445
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:40,800
Useless.

446
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:43,400
Split up and search every room.

447
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:48,360
Wait.

448
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,040
Nee.

449
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:57,400
Nee.

450
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:01,840
Nee. Break it down.

451
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,560
Why are all of you barging in here?

452
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:15,280
Someone broke into the house.

453
00:34:17,159 --> 00:34:18,280
I called you.

454
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:19,639
Are you deaf or what?

455
00:34:20,639 --> 00:34:22,280
I was listening to music.

456
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:40,199
Let go.

457
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:43,719
I'm naked, you know.

458
00:34:44,239 --> 00:34:46,080
Naked naked.

459
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:48,880
Are you sure
you want me to uncover myself, Auntie?

460
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,679
All right then.

461
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:57,200
That's easy enough.

462
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:58,320
Shameless.

463
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:00,640
You want to show them or what?

464
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:02,440
Go search outside.

465
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:04,040
Go.

466
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:10,360
Stay in here.

467
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:11,320
Don't go anywhere.

468
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,960
I'm leaving quietly.

469
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:29,000
If you make a sound, I guarantee
there'll be a hole through your chest.

470
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,400
Mr. Yai, stop acting.

471
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:37,880
I already know everything.

472
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:57,680
Nee,

473
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:01,120
you're not alone.

474
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:04,480
You still have Pin, Yai,

475
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:05,920
and…

476
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,400
and…

477
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:12,360
me too.

478
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:15,640
That's the whole gang,
just like when we were kids.

479
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:19,720
But you were all going to kill me
to get revenge on Auntie.

480
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:22,520
That was just part of the plan.

481
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,920
We were afraid that
if we told you the truth,

482
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,680
you wouldn't agree to help.

483
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,440
You idiot!

484
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:31,040
I was so scared!

485
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:32,880
You all saw me as a tool.

486
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:35,040
Did you ever even think about how I felt?

487
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:36,480
Wait, it's not like that, Nee.

488
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,920
Calm down.

489
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:42,320
It's not like that, Nee.

490
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:45,600
To us, you're very important.

491
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,960
If it weren't for you,
we might all be dead now.

492
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:55,400
You told the truth
that your mother killed Aunt Un.

493
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:58,200
To me,

494
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,400
that was incredibly brave.

495
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:07,160
Am I really worth enough to help you all?

496
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:18,240
It's alright.

497
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:25,200
I agree with Pan.

498
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:28,240
Instead of always running away,
come stand with us.

499
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:29,720
Help us stop your mother.

500
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:33,920
I'll help stop Auntie
from killing anybody else.

501
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:37,600
But if you want me to testify
and send her to prison,

502
00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:39,640
I can't do that.

503
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:43,840
I understand.

504
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:46,480
Just do as much as you want to do.

505
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:48,760
Please take care of Pin.

506
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,440
I did what you told me, Auntie.

507
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:14,240
I didn't go anywhere.

508
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:53,760
Noi. Noi.

509
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,000
Mr. Yai ran this way.

510
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,200
Did you see him?

511
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:59,160
Madam is hunting for Mr. Yai
upstairs right now.

512
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:01,520
He probably isn't hiding in here.

513
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:03,000
- Sommai.
- Yes, ma'am.

514
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:05,080
Take the men and search every exit point.

515
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,840
Jom, go with Sommai.

516
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:07,800
Yes, ma'am.

517
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:10,400
Jom, did you find the intruder?

518
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:11,720
No.

519
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,920
But I think he's still somewhere
on this farm.

520
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:16,040
And how's Mr. Na?

521
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:17,600
Na?

522
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,400
What happened to Na?

523
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:21,560
What is it, Na?

524
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:23,800
Na.

525
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,880
Why did the intruder attack only Na?

526
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:32,480
Jom came in, so he panicked and ran away.

527
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:41,560
Auntie.

528
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:43,560
How are you?

529
00:39:57,200 --> 00:39:58,680
I saw his face.

530
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:01,360
Who was he?

531
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:07,360
Mr. Yai, how did you get in here?

532
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:10,920
Yai is still alive?

533
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:16,760
Pin.

534
00:40:18,240 --> 00:40:19,920
You've been working with Yai, haven't you?

535
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,520
Auntie.

536
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:23,720
Pin has nothing to do with it.

537
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,960
I've been with Mr. Yai for a long time.

538
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:27,400
Even if he hid his face,

539
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,640
if it were really him,
I would recognize him.

540
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:33,760
The build and manner of that masked man
definitely wasn't that of Mr. Yai.

541
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:36,400
Mr. Na must've misheard
and seen something else.

542
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:37,680
Alright.

543
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,680
You come with me.

544
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:43,280
Auntie. Don't.

545
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:48,120
Un,

546
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:50,960
I accepted Pin as my daughter-in-law

547
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:52,840
because I loved you.

548
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:55,560
I saw you as my own older sister.

549
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:58,000
But look at what she's done to me!

550
00:40:58,080 --> 00:40:59,040
She deceived me.

551
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:02,320
She has none of your gratitude,
not even a little.

552
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:04,960
Did you really love my mother?

553
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:08,400
Of course.

554
00:41:09,080 --> 00:41:10,520
That's why I hated Yai so much.

555
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,720
I wanted to kill him with my own hands,

556
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:15,720
because he took Unreuan's life
away from me.

557
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:19,440
If you love your mother,

558
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:21,640
if you care about her,

559
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:24,560
then tell me where Yai is.

560
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:27,480
I really don't know.

561
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:30,240
Since Mr. Yai fell off the cliff,

562
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:32,320
he's never come to see me again.

563
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:38,560
What are you doing?

564
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:41,280
If you still refuse to tell the truth,

565
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,600
I'll dump Un's ashes

566
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:45,080
into the toilet bowl

567
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:47,480
and let her spirit rot and stink in there.

568
00:41:47,560 --> 00:41:48,760
No, Madam.

569
00:41:50,160 --> 00:41:51,920
My mother is already dead.

570
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,000
Won't you let her go even now?

571
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:57,280
Even as a ghost,
she still has to repay what she owes me.

572
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:01,120
If you love Un, then tell me the truth!

573
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:06,080
Let go.

574
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:07,840
Let go.

575
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:10,720
- Let go, Madam.
- You dare fight me, Pin?

576
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:13,400
You have no right to do this to my mother.

577
00:42:16,160 --> 00:42:17,360
Don't, Auntie.

578
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:18,920
Well.

579
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:23,680
I must've been confused.

580
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:25,400
Thinking about it now,

581
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,800
I didn't really see Yai.

582
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,200
What?

583
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,960
When I passed out,

584
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:36,440
I dreamed that Yai was choking me.

585
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:38,600
In the dream, I was terrified.

586
00:42:39,120 --> 00:42:40,200
So when I woke up,

587
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:42,960
I just blurted it out without realizing.

588
00:42:43,040 --> 00:42:44,120
But…

589
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,280
my head hurts, Auntie.

590
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:53,640
- Na.
- I can't remember anything.

591
00:42:53,720 --> 00:42:55,160
Then don't think about it anymore.

592
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,600
I won't press you. Go.

593
00:42:56,680 --> 00:42:57,960
Go back and rest first.

594
00:42:58,040 --> 00:42:59,160
Come on.

595
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:00,200
Let's go.

596
00:43:00,280 --> 00:43:01,760
Go rest.

597
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:03,840
Go. Let's go. Walk slowly.

598
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,160
Pin, how are you?

599
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:10,440
Are you safe?

600
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:11,840
<i>I'm fine.</i>

601
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:14,600
Madam and Jom don't suspect me.

602
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:16,400
You don't have to worry.

603
00:43:16,480 --> 00:43:17,960
But I don't trust Na.

604
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:19,560
He still wants to make you his wife.

605
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:21,040
How am I supposed to rest easily?

606
00:43:21,680 --> 00:43:24,480
It looks like Mr. Na
saw Madam do something,

607
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:25,760
and it scared him.

608
00:43:25,840 --> 00:43:27,480
He was thinking
of running away from the farm.

609
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:32,640
I suspect it has something to do
with Mr. Tong's disappearance.

610
00:43:33,680 --> 00:43:34,920
Mr. Tong disappeared?

611
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:37,320
We searched everywhere.

612
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:38,720
There's not even a shadow of him.

613
00:43:39,400 --> 00:43:41,280
You've run into him several times now.

614
00:43:41,360 --> 00:43:43,240
Do you think it could be Yai?

615
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,800
A few days ago, I almost shot him.

616
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:48,600
But Dad stepped in front
of the bullet for him.

617
00:43:48,680 --> 00:43:51,200
I asked him,
but he still wouldn't admit it was Yai.

618
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,480
Then why didn't you tell me sooner?

619
00:43:54,080 --> 00:43:55,400
I wasn't sure yet.

620
00:43:55,480 --> 00:43:57,160
I was planning to investigate first.

621
00:43:58,240 --> 00:44:00,000
Where is Win now?

622
00:44:00,080 --> 00:44:01,240
Take me to him.

623
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:05,600
I'm not going to do anything
to your father.

624
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:07,280
I just want to ask him to be sure.

625
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:09,840
Hey.

626
00:44:09,920 --> 00:44:11,880
Win is already an old man.

627
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:16,040
Are you going to let your father
wander outside until he dies of old age?

628
00:44:27,960 --> 00:44:28,800
Dad.

629
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:30,560
Uncle Win.

630
00:44:31,560 --> 00:44:33,440
Why did you leave the hospital so soon?

631
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:36,720
Mr. Yai, thank you

632
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:38,480
for hiring a private nurse
to look after me.

633
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:41,080
But I really couldn't stand
lying in bed all day.

634
00:44:41,160 --> 00:44:42,960
I'd rather get out of there
and help you over here.

635
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:48,560
Mr. Yai, what are you doing?

636
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:49,640
Please don't do this.

637
00:44:49,720 --> 00:44:50,880
Let him do it.

638
00:44:50,960 --> 00:44:52,720
Otherwise,
he'll never stop blaming himself.

639
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:58,960
It's me who should apologize to you
on Jom's behalf.

640
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:01,680
I don't consider him my son anymore.

641
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:07,720
Uncle Win, don't do what my dad did.

642
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:10,560
It'll turn into a wound in Jom's heart,

643
00:45:11,160 --> 00:45:12,440
the same way it did for me.

644
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:15,600
It…

645
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:18,080
It hurts so much.

646
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:21,080
Mr. Yai…

647
00:45:21,160 --> 00:45:22,360
Yai.

648
00:45:24,720 --> 00:45:25,760
Chief.

649
00:45:25,840 --> 00:45:27,080
Who's that? What happened?

650
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:28,040
I don't know him either.

651
00:45:28,640 --> 00:45:30,520
I was just about to take him
to the hospital.

652
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:35,040
Mr. Tong?

653
00:45:41,680 --> 00:45:43,040
But if you're impatient,

654
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:44,960
<i>you could just write a will yourself.</i>

655
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:46,680
<i>Type it out and forge the signature.</i>

656
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:49,920
And do you think Mr. Na would be happy
knowing his mother is a murderer?

657
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,800
You're starting to know too much.

658
00:45:51,880 --> 00:45:53,840
Yai is here. Bring everyone in.

659
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,120
Now.

660
00:45:57,080 --> 00:45:58,400
Yai!

661
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:01,960
On's pregnant?

662
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:03,400
<i>On had a miscarriage because of you.</i>

663
00:46:03,480 --> 00:46:05,080
You killed your own child.

664
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:49,440
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
